text: But to understand how it works, we first need to start with its closest relative; The Number Line.

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/But_to_understand_how_it_works,_we_first_need_to_start_with_its_closest_relative;_The_Number_Line.pt

video: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/clip_0022.mp4

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/You_remember_how_a_number_line_works,_right?.pt

video: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/clip_0023.mp4
text: A number line starts at zero, and represents positive numbers as you move to the right and negative numbers as you more to the left.

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/A_number_line_starts_at_zero,_and_represents_positive_numbers_as_you_move_to_the_right_and_negative_numbers_as_you_more_to_the_left.pt

text: And there's usually marks showing where each integer is along the way.

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/And_there's_usually_marks_showing_where_each_integer_is_along_the_way.pt

text: Now imagine cloning that number line and rotating the copy counter-clockwise by 90 degrees so that the second number line is perpendicular to the first and they intersect at their zero points.

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/Now_imagine_cloning_that_number_line_and_rotating_the_copy_counter-clockwise_by_90_degrees_so_that_the_second_number_line_is_perpendicular_to_the_first_and_they_intersect_at_their_zero_points.pt

text: What we have now is a "number plane". It's basically like a 2-Dimensional version of a number line, but that second dimension makes it much more useful.

text: With a simple 1-Dimensional number line, we could show where various numbers were located along that line by drawing (or plotting) points.

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/With_a_simple_1-Dimensional_number_line,_we_could_show_where_various_numbers_were_located_along_that_line_by_drawing_(or_plotting)_points.pt

text: Okay, to understand how coordinates work, remember that our number plane is formed by combining two perpendicular number lines.

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/From_now_on,_we're_going_to_refer_to_each_one_of_these_number_lines_as_an_"axis".pt

video: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/clip_0041.mp4
text: One of the axes is horizontal (like the horizon) which means the other axis is vertical (or straight up and down).

text: And they're often called the "horizontal" and "vertical" axes because of that.

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/And_they're_often_called_the_"horizontal"_and_"vertical"_axes_because_of_that.pt

text: But even more often, the axes are referred to by variable-based names.

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/But_even_more_often,_the_axes_are_referred_to_by_variable-based_names.pt

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/Why_use_variable_names?.pt

video: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/clip_0046.mp4
text: Well there's two good reasons.

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/Well_there's_two_good_reasons.pt

video: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/clip_0047.mp4
text: The first is that variable names are more flexible than horizontal and vertical, which relate to a specific orientation in space that may not always be relevant.
video_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/clip_0047.pt
text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/The_first_is_that_variable_names_are_more_flexible_than_horizontal_and_vertical,_which_relate_to_a_specific_orientation_in_space_that_may_not_always_be_relevant.pt

video: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/clip_0048.mp4
text: And the second reason is that each of the two coordinate numbers is actually a variable that relates to a specific position along one of the two axes of the coordinate plane.
video_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/clip_0048.pt
text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/And_the_second_reason_is_that_each_of_the_two_coordinate_numbers_is_actually_a_variable_that_relates_to_a_specific_position_along_one_of_the_two_axes_of_the_coordinate_plane.pt

video: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/clip_0049.mp4
text: And since those variables are usually called 'X' and 'Y', it makes sense to name the two axes the same way.

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/And_since_those_variables_are_usually_called_'X'_and_'Y',_it_makes_sense_to_name_the_two_axes_the_same_way.pt

video: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/clip_0050.mp4
text: The first coordinate number listed will be called 'X' and the second coordinate number listed will be called 'Y'.
video_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/clip_0050.pt
text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/The_first_coordinate_number_listed_will_be_called_'X'_and_the_second_coordinate_number_listed_will_be_called_'Y'.pt

text: And we're always going to list the numbers in that same order, 'X' first and then 'Y', so that we never get confused about which is which.

text_latent: ./clip_video/Algebra Basics： Graphing On The Coordinate Plane - Math Antics [9Uc62CuQjc4]/videos/And_we're_always_going_to_list_the_numbers_in_that_same_order,_'X'_first_and_then_'Y',_so_that_we_never_get_confused_about_which_is_which.pt

text: To understand how the slope of a line relates to the equation of the line, let's introduce a common form for linear equations, Y equals MX plus B.
